replyContent:
Hi Harvey! 
Thanks for your review and feedback. Indeed, some firmwares revisions (such as r21061) reportedly have non-working SSH servers - this is written in both the Play Store app description and the "FAQ" section of the app website ( http://goo.gl/jVjeqx ). But perhaps not stressed enough..
Anyways, glad to hear you sorted it out.
Best.

This app makes it very easy to connect to remote or local DD-WRT routers from your phone for monitoring and maintenance.  If you have gone to the trouble of putting DD-WRT onto your router, you owe it to yourself to try this app!  Well worth the $4 price tag (at the time of this review).  Word of warning: there is a "Lite" version of this app, but it is not representative of the experience of the paid app: WAY too many ads (even for a "Lite" app), and frequent crashes.  Try the pro version instead; you can request a refund from Google within 2 hours of purchase if you don't like it.
Works well with my R7000 running DD WRT

Had to buy the non add version.  Very nice app and companion to the dd-wrt webui.  Works with the latest beta builds of dd-wrt.

I now have Wi-Fi on almost 25acres and this app lets me monitor it all. Excellent app!!

Thank you!
